nerations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJewszUkrainezChernivt︠s︡ixHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszUkrainezChernivt︠s︡ixSocial life and customsy20th century. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  acarpathian mountains.  acommunal memoir.  acultural identity.  acultural memory.  aczernowitz.  adiscussion books.  adispersed people.  aeastern european culture.  aeducation.  aengaging.  aeuropean culture.  afamily history.  afamily.  agenerational.  ahabsburg empire.  ahistorical account.  aholocaust.  aidealized place.  ajewish czernowitz.  ajewish german.  ajewish memory.  amultigenerational.  anonfiction.  aoral history.  apersonal history.  aromania.  aukraine.  avanished community.  aworld war ii.  awwii.1 aSpitzer, Leo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025772640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094490940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944909423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944909/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY